# Sealed audit-proof artifacts are byte-immutable: their hash chain commits over
# the exact bytes of each entry. Any line-ending conversion (autocrlf on Windows
# checkout) or in-place text substitution (codemods, renames) changes those bytes
# and invalidates the seal — `pangolin verify` then correctly reports TAMPERED.
#
# Marking them `-text` disables EOL conversion so they round-trip byte-for-byte on
# every platform. Do NOT run repo-wide find-replace over these files; regenerate
# them from a fresh run instead. (Background: the Agora->Pangolin rename rewrote
# `agora://`->`pangolin://` inside a committed bundle and broke its verify.)
examples/**/bundle.json -text
examples/**/verify-context.json -text
